In early December 2023 the KSC imposed restrictions on visits to Thaçi, Veseli and Selimi in detention, citing alleged attempts to interfere with witnesses and obstruct their testimonies. On 14 December the KSC Appeals Panel upheld the 2022 conviction of Salih Mustafa. By that time Kosovo prosecutors were reported to have filed 33 war crimes indictments since 2018, charging a total of 89 suspects (including 
in absentia
).
